      "width": 420,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Define Workflow Contracts",
        "body": "Define the minimum fields and edge semantics for `trigger`, `action`, `condition`, `input`, `output`, and `branch`. The first package slice now exists under `/library/classes/nodes/workflow-execution`, with explicit class artifacts, a bridge-first package root, and a canonical template.",
        "status": "done",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "priority": "high",
        "estimateHours": "3",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "Each v1 type has a minimal contract",
          "Execution order and branching semantics are explicit",
          "The graph calls out where typed edges are mandatory"
